# Backend Python: use uv

Always run backend Python tools through `uv` from `backend/`. Never invoke system `python`, `alembic`, `pytest`, `ruff`, or `mypy` directly on the host.

## Preferred

```bash
cd backend
uv run alembic upgrade head
uv run pytest -q
uv run ruff check app tests
uv run python -m app.seeds.prompts --days 30
```

With Railway env injected:

```bash
cd backend
railway run uv run alembic upgrade head
railway run uv run python -m app.seeds.prompts --days 30
```

Make targets (`make db-migrate`, `make seed`, etc.) already go through `uv run`.

## Exceptions

- Production/runtime Docker image (`backend/Dockerfile`): packages are installed on `PATH`; `railway.toml` `releaseCommand` may call `alembic` directly inside the container.
- Dev Compose image already uses `uv` (`Dockerfile.dev` / `dev-entrypoint.sh`).
